  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0db4\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dba \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9a \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "One-day passport service in three more districts",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The one-day passport issuance service will be available in three more districts from next Monday (4), said Investment Promotion Minister Dhammika Perera.",
        "Accordingly, the issuance of passports under the one day service will commence from next Monday from the offices of the Department of Immigration and Emigration in Matara, Kandy and Vavuniya, the Minister said.",
        "Dhammika Perera also said that the one year visa valid for foreigners married to Sri Lankans will be extended to 5 years.",
        "Dhammika Perera, Hon. Minister of Investment Promotion, visited the Department of Immigration and Emigration today (29) and said that these steps will be taken to address the problems faced by the public who come to seek its services.",
        "Minister Dhammika Perera also said that a separate counter will be opened at the Head Office of the Department of Immigration and Emigration in Suhurupaya, Battaramulla to issue passports to those who have completed the required documents to go for foreign employment.",
        "Accordingly, those who have the relevant documents can go to this special counter and obtain their passports without having to wait in the usual queue, the Minister said.",
        "The Minister also took steps to provide a photocopying database to the Department of Immigration and Emigration at his own expense at a cost of Rs. have.",
        "The number of tourists arriving in the country should be announced daily on the social media network Twitter from next Monday (4) and accordingly the number of tourists who arrived the previous day will be announced every day from next Monday at 9.00 am on the Twitter account of the Department of Immigration and Emigration.",
        "The Minister said that the importation of foreign exchange through the 'Golden Paradise' visa program proposed to the government by Dhammika Perera before he became a Minister was still being delayed due to the fact that the Central Bank of Sri Lanka has not yet given approval to commercial banks to accept such deposits.",
        "Mr. Dhammika Perera stated that discussions will be held with the Central Bank officials in this regard and a solution will be worked out expeditiously."
      ],
